INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (96551, 'Leaders don''t pray to God to fill their potholes. They ask God for shovels so they can do it by His grace. Pray practically.', 3301, 0), (96552, 'The main way people waste time is by complaining of their past wasted time. Leaders respond even if it seems to be late.', 3301, 0), (96553, 'To leaders, one trusted friend is better than ten well known betrayers', 3301, 0), (96554, 'What differentiates victors and victims are visions and vigor. Victims won''t get the vim to step out of their situations.', 3301, 0), (96555, 'Inferior and Superior life lives in the interior of a person.', 3301, 0), (96556, 'Experiment participants asked to pick which politician looked more confident in a photograph picked the winner of the race two thirds of the time. This phenomenon held up even when they only glimpsed the photographs for a 10th of a second.', 2838, 0), (96557, 'Leaders don''t define wealth by material things they see. They define wealth by the visions they imagine and actions they take.', 3301, 0), (96558, 'Leaders act with visions', 19644, 0), (96559, 'He uses the nice old words so rich in tradition to be sure I know he means it.', 1265, 0), (96560, 'There are proven ways to win the loyalty of tough, strong, ferocious men: play on the certain knowledge of their superiority, the mystique of secret covenant, the esprit of shared suffering.', 1265, 0), (96561, 'Clarity repositions you to quit nice activities that take you nowhere in order to pursue risky tasks that take you somewhere.', 3301, 0), (96562, 'Leaders get to tall heights by taking short steps. Being faithful, diligent and consistent with little steps is the secret to mounting greater heights.', 3301, 0), (96563, 'Leaders with high esteem are high performers.', 3301, 0), (96564, 'Richest leaders are not those who have calories in their bank accounts', 19645, 0), (96565, 'Leaders let go of what they can''t control. It''s a matter of knowing the power of the muscles and bones in your neck so you can go for what it can carry', 3301, 0), (96566, 'Leaders should know how fast time runs and how faster they can beat it. Poor leaders run slowly till time overtakes them.', 3301, 0), (96567, 'Leaders take actions. Attacking your plans with blows of actions will not cost you painful but temporal bruises. Never leave goals untouched.', 3301, 0), (96568, 'Achievements take leaders'' name everywhere. Character keeps those names wherever they reach. A leader with no trust soon fades no matter how far he goes.', 3301, 0), (96569, 'Leaders don''t cheat', 19646, 0), (96570, 'Those who see poverty looking for human slaves to capture, will tell you they saw him holding the handcuffs of laziness.', 3301, 0), (96571, 'Self-leadership is about digging out your hidden endowment and making them known and useful to those who need it most.', 3301, 0), (96572, 'Vision unknown is self-abuse. Vision known is self-abuse discovery. But vision applied is self-liberation. Application is the key', 3301, 0), (96573, 'Leaders reject free opportunities they don''t need, so that they can have time to create the expensive opportunities they need.', 3301, 0), (96574, 'Shallow are the souls that have forgotten how to shudder. Leon Cass', 2838, 0), (96575, 'Talk about presidents "taking" the country hither and yon is part of the foam of presidential elections.', 2252, 0), (96576, 'The feelings of politicians are rarely transparent.', 11776, 0), (96577, 'The author characterizes Hamilton''s tone in the Federalist papers by saying that he never spoke of problems but of being at the last stage in the crisis.', 11776, 0), (96578, 'A boss says “go and make sure you do it”', 19647, 0), (96579, 'A person with low standards will forever be walking. A person with high standard will soon stop walking and start running. Later, they’ll soon stop running and start galloping. The next time you see him, he’s either flying or soaring.', 3301, 0), (96580, 'Leaders learn more from blames than praises. Praises make them know what’s already done well', 19648, 0), (96581, 'Leaders try every possible means to leave the world better than they found it. They make an indelible impact and society remembers them for that.', 3301, 0), (96582, 'Don’t let the horrible nature of the waters prevent you from crossing the rivers of life. The more horrible the challenges we face, the sweeter the joy of conquering them.', 3301, 0), (96583, 'Leaders are raised through training and experience. Nobody was born naturally with hand-gloves of leadership. We come to life to search for it, discover it and optimize it.', 3301, 0), (96584, 'Live an exemplary life as a leader. When you are gone, you will still lead from the grave because your influence, impacts and inspirations will become and information for the living.', 3301, 0), (96585, 'You can’t gather much if you won’t go on risk expedition. Leaders never fear the thorns', 19649, 0), (96586, 'People do not recognize that you can do it when you merely tell them you can. Until they see you doing it, they won’t follow you. Leaders who are willing to go further alone today are those to be consulted for solutions tomorrow.', 3301, 0), (96587, 'Leaders look out for people who can criticize them constructively and rebuke them reasonably.', 3301, 0), (96588, 'Leaders create and maintain good interpersonal relationships with people they meet and work with. People who lead better relate better.', 3301, 0), (96589, 'If you have only answers and no questions, chances are high that you will never know new things.', 3301, 0), (96590, 'Contrary to popular opinion, leaders aren’t created out of fame. Fame is just a shadow. When you enter dark times in, it leaves you.', 3301, 0), (96591, 'Leaders know where they can function better. They don’t cry over what they cannot do.', 3301, 0), (96592, 'Innovation is the art of creating a better, a more convenient and more comfortable way for the world to pass. Leaders leave 