in. They embrace the pain.', 3301, 0), (96814, 'The ladder of leadership can only stand firm on the grounds of integrity. Any other ground makes it unstable till it falls.', 3301, 0), (96815, 'Africa PRODUCES what it does NOT CONSUME and CONSUMES what it does NOT PRODUCE.', 19689, 0), (96816, 'Leaders don''t venture without vision. They don''t pray without plans. They don''t climb without clues. They are always prepared.', 3301, 0), (96817, 'Leaders don''t climb hills of success with shoes of pride. They are slippery enough to bring a person down to the valley.', 3301, 0), (96818, 'Bridges take people across rivers. Leaders take people across ignorance. With a leader, the destination of a journey is sure.', 3301, 0), (96819, 'Leaders will love to be poor and see their people rich, than to be rich and see their people poor. This is their mission.', 3301, 0), (96820, 'Fear punches holes in your eyes so that you don''t see the future clearly. Faith enlarges your vision to behold your destiny.', 3301, 0), (96821, 'By constant practices, deliberate repetitions and uninterrupted exercises, leaders go from zero to hero. They don''t quit.', 3301, 0), (96822, 'If you''re determined to stand, nothing can move you. If you''re determined to move, nothing can stop you. Determination is the key!', 3301, 0), (96823, 'Don''t confuse one leader''s bluster for muster or another leader''s meekness for weakness.', 7677, 0), (96824, 'You don''t necessarily need atomic bombs to destroy a nation. Politicians who value their pockets than the life of citizens always do that every day.', 3301, 0), (96825, 'So often in the church, being a pastor or a "spiritual leader" means being the example of  "godly living." A pastor is supposed to be the person who is really good at this Christianity stuff — the person others can look to as an example of righteousness. But as much as being the person who is the best Christian, who "follows Jesus" the most closely can feel a little seductive, it''s simply